          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 04</h1><p><strong>Questions 35 - 40</strong></p><p>For each question, choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct letters (from <strong>A - E</strong>) and write them in any order in answer boxes.</p><p>Which TWO technical differences between Japanese bullet trains and French TGV trains are mentioned?</p><p>35</p><p>36</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The fuel they use.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The number of coaches, or cars, that make up a train.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    The location of the power source.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    The presence or absence of locomotive engines to pull the train.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    The weight of the locomotives they use.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which TWO differences in operating conditions for trains in Europe and Japan are mentioned?</p><p>37</p><p>38</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The number of tracks a train runs on.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The altitude above sea level of train tracks.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    The ground over which train tracks are laid.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    The distance between stops.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    The number of passengers carried.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which TWO advantages of the bullet train's power system are mentioned?</p><p>39</p><p>40</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    This method uses less power than other systems.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The motors can be used to stop the train as well as to move it.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It enables frequent increases or decreases in the train's speed.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    It doesn't require regular maintenance.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    It is safer than any other power system.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
